english:
  title: Following the Rhyme of Yeonsan Pavilion
  author: Park Jin-nok
  language: eng
  text: |-
    Along the cliff a narrow path appears and disappears.
    The ancient town leans on mountains—the mountains themselves became its walls.
    Rough and stony fields greet the early snow,
    While steep pine-clad paths wind into the clouds.

    I wish to live in seclusion, yet I have no true plan,
    And though I speak of leaving office, it seems my heart is not in it.
    These past few days the prefecture has few duties—
    Lowering the blinds, reclining in the heights, I find clarity at last.
